President of the United States, Donald Trump has been accused of several things some of which is as a result of his tweets. After Nike sports brand made Colin Kaepernick, the first NLF player to kneel during the national anthem to protest racial prejudice, their brand ambassador, the president took to Twitter to expressly state that the sports company had sent “a terrible message”. Now, his latest friend, Kanye West (now known as Ye) and proud supporter is asking NFL quarterback Colin Kaepernick (you read right) to speak directly with the president of the United States. reaching out to Colin Kaepernick. I would like you to speak with the president to tell him your experience directly. Let’s have a dialogue not a diatribe. — ye (@kanyewest) October 3, 2018  If you were wondering what a diatribe means, it is “a forceful and bitter verbal attack against something”. Over to you Kaepernick!